ed in the enterprise from the start—explores their efforts and shows how their approach provides a model for achieving systemic change. Chronicling the group’s progress along an uncharted path, he shows how people with a variety of skills and personalities collaborate to get things done. Through their work, Hamm examines some of today’s most important technologies and concepts, such as systems thinking and modeling, complexity theory, artificial intelligence, and new thinking about resilience. The book features vivid, informal profiles of a number of the group’s members and brings to life the excitement and energy of dynamic, smart people trying to change the world.Part journal of a plague year and part call to action, The Pivot tells the remarkable story of a collaborative experiment seeking to make the world more sustainable and resilient.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aSocial action. 0aSocial change. 0aSocial problems. 7aBUSINESS & ECONOMICS / Development / Sustainable Development.2bisacsh1 aAlafandi, Waël, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBay, Paola, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFlyntz, Kristin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHershkovitz, Shay, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMabbett, Ian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMim, Sharmin Shara, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMorris-Evans, Shulamit, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNguyen, Anh, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPanagiotou, Anna, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRossiter, Tom, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/